        <h2>About SwiftSync: Your Personal Music Upload Platform</h2>

        <p><strong>SwiftSync</strong> is a web-based application designed to provide a platform for users to upload, manage, and enjoy their personal music collections. Inspired by the sleek design of popular streaming services, SwiftSync focuses on offering an intuitive and user-friendly experience for music enthusiasts.</p>

        <h3>Key Features</h3>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Music Uploads:</strong> Users can upload their music files by filling out a simple form that includes:
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Track Title:</strong> The name of the song.</li>
                    <li><strong>MP3 File:</strong> Upload MP3 files directly.</li>
                    <li><strong>Album Cover:</strong> Optionally upload an image for the album cover.</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li><strong>Dynamic Music Library:</strong> After uploading, tracks are displayed in a personal library section, showcasing album covers and song titles.</li>
            <li><strong>Manage Your Library:</strong> Users can delete songs they no longer want, ensuring a tidy and organized music collection.</li>
        </ol>

        <h3>Technology Stack</h3>
        <p>SwiftSync is developed using the following technologies:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for a seamless user experience.</li>
            <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Utilizes Node.js and Express for server-side logic and handling file uploads.</li>
            <li><strong>Database:</strong> A database (MySQL) is used to store user data and music metadata.</li>
        </ul>
